						<summary>

						<p>Slab in front of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1466, Krōdhi, Kārttīka, śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1544 A.D. October 30.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of four looms <hi rend="italic">(maggālu)</hi> free of the <hi rend="italic">Siddhāya</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kāṇike</hi> taxes to god Janārdanadēva of Saṅkēpalle by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍlēśvara</hi> Varadarājula China Veṅgaḷayyadēva Mahārāju, who held Gutti-<hi rend="italic">sīma</hi> as <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara</hi> from Aḷiya Rāmarājayya Mahārāju.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh; Cuddapah District,</hi> Part II, No. 166.]</p>						

						</summary>
